<Defs>

    <ThingDef Abstract="true" ParentName="ApparelMakeableBase" Name="CVN_BP_OnSkinBase">
    	<techLevel>Industrial</techLevel>
        <graphicData>
            <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
            <shaderType>CutoutComplex</shaderType>
            <drawSize>1.3</drawSize>
        </graphicData>
        <thingCategories>
            <li>Apparel</li>
        </thingCategories>
        <recipeMaker>
            <recipeUsers Inherit="false">
                <li>CVN_BP_FabricationBench</li>
            </recipeUsers>
        </recipeMaker>
		<uiIconScale>1.6</uiIconScale>
    </ThingDef>

    <ThingDef ParentName="CVN_BP_OnSkinBase">
        <defName>BP_Fatigues</defName>
        <label>Sirdar fatigues</label>
        <recipeMaker>
		    <researchPrerequisites>
			 <li>GW_BP_Basic</li>
			</researchPrerequisites>
            <skillRequirements>
                <Crafting>4</Crafting>
            </skillRequirements>
            <displayPriority>418</displayPriority>
        </recipeMaker>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/Sirdar/Onskin/BP_SirdarSkin_Male_south</texPath>
        </graphicData>
		<stuffCategories>
            <li>Fabric</li>
        </stuffCategories>
	    <description>Standard Imperial Guard fatigues that have seen better times, now pressed into service of the Blood Pact. These were likely kept after desertion or taken from a fallen soldier. \n\nThe battle-hardened Blood Pact were the core of the Chaos resistance forces in the Sabbat Worlds Crusade, fighting with a disciple unusual for Chaos cultists.</description>
        <costStuffCount>85</costStuffCount>
        <statBases>
            <MaxHitPoints>110</MaxHitPoints>
            <WorkToMake>4000</WorkToMake>
			<Mass>2</Mass>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.4</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>0.50</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>0.25</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>
        </statBases>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/Sirdar/Onskin/BP_SirdarSkin</wornGraphicPath>
			<useWornGraphicMask>true</useWornGraphicMask>		
            <countsAsClothingForNudity>true</countsAsClothingForNudity>
            <bodyPartGroups>
                <li>Torso</li>
                <li>Legs</li>
                <li>Shoulders</li>
                <li>Arms</li>
				<li>Feet</li>
            </bodyPartGroups>
            <layers>
                <li>OnSkin</li>
            </layers>
            <tags>
                <li>BPapparelskin1</li>
            </tags>
        </apparel>
    </ThingDef>
	
	<ThingDef ParentName="CVN_BP_OnSkinBase">
        <defName>BP_DBfatigues</defName>
        <label>Death tunic</label>
        <recipeMaker>
		    <researchPrerequisites>
			 <li>GW_BP_Vanguard</li>
			</researchPrerequisites>
            <skillRequirements>
                <Crafting>4</Crafting>
            </skillRequirements>
            <displayPriority>419</displayPriority>
        </recipeMaker>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/DeathBrigade/Onskin/BP_DeathBOnskin_Male_south</texPath>
        </graphicData>
		<stuffCategories>
		    <li>Leathery</li>
        </stuffCategories>
	    <description>Taking on a more ceremonial appearance, these tunic-like fatigues are worn by senior members of the Pact. The Death Brigade often serves at the vanguard of Blood Pact assaults and is a equivalent of Imperial Guard Storm Troopers. They are the most skilled and the most feared of all Blood Pact units.</description>
        <costStuffCount>125</costStuffCount>
        <statBases>
            <MaxHitPoints>125</MaxHitPoints>
            <WorkToMake>6500</WorkToMake>
			<Mass>2</Mass>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.5</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>0.55</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>0.20</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>
        </statBases>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/DeathBrigade/Onskin/BP_DeathBOnskin</wornGraphicPath>
			<useWornGraphicMask>true</useWornGraphicMask>		
            <countsAsClothingForNudity>true</countsAsClothingForNudity>
            <bodyPartGroups>
                <li>Torso</li>
                <li>Legs</li>
                <li>Shoulders</li>
                <li>Arms</li>
				<li>Feet</li>
            </bodyPartGroups>
            <layers>
                <li>OnSkin</li>
            </layers>
            <tags>
                <li>BPapparelskin2</li>
            </tags>
        </apparel>
    </ThingDef>
	
